The following Privacy Policy (“
Privacy Policy
”) is written by Panini S.p.A. – headquartered in Modena, Italy, viale Emilio Po 380 – 41126, Tel. +39 059 382111 - Fax +39 059 827431 (hereinafter “
Panini
”) as Data Controller of the personal data collected, provided directly by you or generated by us as a result of processing of the website
www.paninidigitalcollections.com
(hereinafter "
Website
") and of the application Panini Digital Collections for smartphone and tablet (hereinafter "
Application
" or "
App
") for the collection of the digital sticker albums released by Panini. Please remember this document is available also on third party platforms, on the "Stores, or through these ones is accessible anyway. Website and Application are collectively referred as “Applications” in this privacy policy.
Panini considers your privacy essential. We therefore ask you to read this information carefully in order to make a freely given, specific, informed and unambiguous choice.
This Privacy Policy is divided into sections (hereinafter collectively "
Sections
” and/or individually "
Section
”), each of them dealing a specific topic, so that you can immediately find what you are looking for and concentrate your attention on the topic of interest. The Website or the Application may contain links to other websites and/or smartphone applications. Panini is not responsible for privacy practices or the content of such websites and/or smartphone applications.
In general, all the personal data (hereinafter “
Personal Data
” and/or “
Data
”) collected by Panini or given by you when you use services provided by the Website and the Applications (hereinafter “
Services
” or individually "
Service
", as better defined inside Purpose n. 1 called "Services Provision" of section
C "Purposes of the Personal Data Processing" of this Privacy Policy
) as fully described in the following section
“C. Purposes of Personal Data Processing”
of this Privacy Policy, will be processed lawfully and in a transparent manner in accordance with the principles stated in the current legislation on the protection of personal data, such as transparency, fairness, lawfulness, data minimisation, purpose limitation, accuracy, storage limitation, integrity and confidentiality.
This Privacy Policy is written on the basis of the transparency principle using a simple and not too legal language to increase the level of understanding of the statements given.
A- Type of Personal Data Processed
Panini does not require Personal Data for the purposes of browsing the main sections of its website and Applications. However, some of our Applications contain special and privileged sections for registered users.
Name, Last name, Contact Details and other Personal Data
When you create an account to log into the Website or Application, Panini may ask your personal information such as: name, last name, gender, contact details, month and year of birth, county or state, and country of residence.
For users who have an account, the Data collected will be: username randomly generated by randomly combining common sense words, statistical information on the use of the Application and the Website (e.g. the last time an access was made, including the IP address), device ID (for authentication), identifier used within the registration system to identify the user, activation of codes, collections in which you participate, opening of packages, insertion of stickers within the albums you are collecting, the balance of coins purchased or obtained, information on purchases made (digital and physical), user ID. Application usage data such as albums collected, exchanges made. For guest users (i.e. users who do not have an account), the Data collected by the Application or Website are: statistical information on the use of the Application and Site (e.g. the last time it was accessed, including IP address), device ID (for authentication purposes), as well as "Your Device Data" as identified in the relevant paragraph below.
If you decide to purchase the printed version of the digital sticker collection you have collected, you may be asked to indicate other Data such as: shipping address, billing address, phine number, the payment method and the shipping method. In that occasion, with regard to the payment data that you have transmitted to us, Panini undertakes to process only the data received by digital payment companies and credit card payment organisations, which consists exclusively of information relating to the payment status (accepted/refused). All additional information relating to bank accounts, prepaid cards or credit cards is recorded by the company that manages the corresponding service, and it is not authorised to use the Personal Data received through it for other purposes.
Further Personal Data may be collected during the management of each relationship may consist of those that you decide to provide to Panini through the use of the Contact Us area available on the Applications. Some sections of the Website or Application and the nature of the communications you freely decide to send us via the electronic or physical addresses on the Website or App envisage empty text boxes, in which you can give Panini information, which may contain Personal Data. Being free fields, you may choose to communicate (even inadvertently) particular categories of Personal Data, such as those revealing political opinions, religious or philosophical beliefs, or union membership, as well as genetic data, biomedical data which can permit to uniquely identify a specific person, data related to health or sex life or sexual orientation.
Panini asks you not to disclose any of these types of data, unless you consider it strictly necessary to pursue the request you forward to us. Since the indication of such information is, as said, totally optional, if you choose to do so, Panini could process such data only with your explicit consent and in compliance with the current legislation. Panini, therefore, underlines the importance of expressing your explicit consent to the processing of these particular categories of Personal Data in case you decide to share them with Panini.
Personal Data of Third Parties
As mentioned in the previous paragraph, when you use the Application you may upload digital pictures depicting other people and/or include written content that in fact may contain Personal Data relating also to other people. In all cases in which you decide to share such Data, you will be considered a self-appointed Data Controller and, as such, you will have to assume all the relevant legal obligations and responsibilities. Therefore, in this regard, you undertake to hold Panini harmless from any dispute, claim, request for compensation for damage from data treatment etc. that could reach Panini from people whose Personal Data have been forwarded by you in violation of the applicable rules on the protection of Personal Data.
As, in such cases, Panini does not collect this information directly from the data subjects (but indirectly from you), you guarantee that this specific treatment can be based on the consent of these data subjects or on another suitable lawful basis that legitimizes the processing of the information in question
Online payment data
With regard to the Data relating to the payment that you have transmitted to us, Panini undertakes to process only the data received by digital payment companies and credit card payment organisations, which consist exclusively of information relating to the payment status (accepted/refused). All additional information relating to bank accounts, prepaid cards or credit cards is recorded by the company that manages the corresponding service, and it is not authorised to use Data for other purposes the Personal Data received through the Website or the Application for other purposes. For the privacy information relating to the order payments processed by Apple and Google, please refer to
www.apple.com/legal/privacy/data/en/app-store/
and
policies.google.com/privacy?hl=en-US
Social Login
You can also access the Site and the Application using your personal credentials from one of the social networks included in the registration module. In this case, the social network will automatically send your personal data to Panini. You will only be asked to enter any data necessary to complete the registration and which is not provided by the social network. To find out what Data the social network will share with Panini refer to the Privacy Policy of the social network through which you are accessing and the data sharing options that it indicates. Additionally, please note that in such cases Panini will provide specific privacy information, the latest version of which is always available
by clicking here
.
IP address spatial coordinates
When you create a profile on the Site or through the Application, we will collect the approximate spatial coordinates (state, city) of your IP address associated, only, with your last log-in. We will keep this information only to the extent strictly necessary and proportionate to ensure the purpose of Security, therefore for the sole purpose of obtaining information necessary to identify anomalies, fraudulent activities and/or abuse in the use and access to the Site and the Application.
Navigation Data and Cookies
The computer systems and software used to run the Website acquire, during their normal operation, some Personal Data whose transmission is implicit in the use of Internet communication protocols. This information is not collected by Panini to be associated with identified data subjects, but by its very nature could, through processing and association with data held by third parties, allow data subjects to be identified. This category of data includes the IP addresses or domain names of the computers used by the users connecting to the Website, the addresses in URI (Uniform Resource Identifier) notation of the requested services, the time of the request, the method used in submitting the request to the server, the size of the file obtained in response, the numerical code indicating the status of the response given by the server (good result, error, etc.) and other parameters related to the operating system and the user's computer.
The information on the use of cookies is available in our Cookie Policy, which we kindly ask you to read by clicking on the following symbol
and/or
(Manage Cookies)
in the Website footer.
Data of your device (applicable when you use the Application)
By selecting the option "Install" in the App Store, you authorise Panini to access certain Personal Data and other information on your mobile device ("Device"), which is essential for a successful installation (e.g. Device model,  Device ID of the mobile device, in case you are using an iOS or Android device, for the purpose of sending any service push notifications, session duration, operative system of the Device, date of first launch, Application openings, Application updates, purchases made through the Application, screen resolution, type of network connection, language, etc.) Sharing this information is essential to install the App and you can stop it by removing the App from your Device.
SDK and tracking technologies (applicable when you use the App)
SDK (Software Development Kit) and similar technologies are information the mobile apps record and/or read on your Device. These technologies usually enable the use of a mobile app to be analysed in order to avoid malfunctions and improve user experience
Via the App, Panini uses SKD and similar technologies supplied by third parties, depending on the circumstances, as autonomous data controllers compared to Panini (using the Data they collect for their own purposes and according to the terms and conditions they have established) or as Data Processors (using the Personal Data on behalf of Panini)
For further information on how these third parties can use your data, please read their privacy policies:
SDK
Description
ML Kit library
For QR code scanner. It is used to extract the QR code information, no personal data passed to the library.
https://developers.google.com/ml-kit/
