https://www.adyen.com/policies-and-disclaimer/privacy-policy
Please note that, with reference to the SDKs that allow you to access the Site or the Application using the personal account of one of the social networks included in the registration form, Panini will provide specific privacy information, the latest version of which is always available
by clicking here
.
B- Personal Data Processing of Children below the Age of 18 Years
The use of the Services included in the Website and in the Application are reserved to people whose age is above 18 years .
Users who do not declare the age will be considered and treated as under 18 and therefore they not will be able to access the sections reserved for registered users of the Website or Application.
Children aged equal or less than 16 years old or, in accordance with national local laws, of a different and suitable age to be able to collect a valid consent, however not less than 14 years old, cannot use the contact form area by themselves and are not authorised to send Personal Data to Panini.
C- Purposes of the Personal Data Processing
We will process your Personal Data for the following purposes:
to allow operations strictly connected and contributory to the management of our relations with you, such as respond to queries received via the contact forms or by Panini (electronically and/or in printed form) at any of the addresses specified on the Website or the App; allow you to access private sections of the Website or App; help if you forget your personal account login/password for the Website or App; executing contracts for the sale of goods and/or services also digital on the Website or on the Application, in-app purchases included (e.g. to get extra digital contents o purchase virtual coins), managing and fulfilling orders of the printed version of the digital albums you collect; allowing you to consult the chronology of your purchases; ensuring the delivery of the purchased products and tracking your order status; to send you communication notices regarding the App via push notifications; send you communications like the upcoming deactivation and deletion of your account
(Provision of services)
;
complying with laws, regulations and EU legislation or with provisions issued by authorities empowered by law and provisions issued by Supervisory and Control Bodies, as well as allowing tax and accounting compliance
(Legal Compliance)
;
to get the information required to identify anomalies, illegal activity and/or abuse of the use of the Websites and App towards Panini or third parties
(Security)
;
sending you, if you are using or have used a service on an Application or if you are buying or you have bought a product or a service through the Application, direct marketing and promotional communication via e-mail about similar products or services
(Soft Spam)
to provide information on our products and/or services, including promotional and commercial activities, market research and marketing or, activities to measure the level of customer satisfaction by sending questionnaires, carrying out surveys or opinion polls. The activity may be carried out by using automated systems without an operator (e.g. email), through the official pages managed by Panini on social networks but also via traditional contact methods (e.g. postal services and telephone); and via the Application push notifications with marketing contents, if you use the Application (
Marketing
)
to set up user groups by processing the data they have provided, by using the third party profiling cookies - if you accept them - on the Website, by collecting and analysing the information on the preferences selected and choices made on the App - if you use it - and via your Device data (e.g. AAIG),so as not to indiscriminately send generalized, commercial and promotional communications to all users and to customize the Services provided via the App, if you use it. This enables us to segment users, creating groups based upon common features for example, on the country of origin, language, gender, previous purchases, etc. This allows us (in case you have simultaneously provided consent for marketing purposes) you to send commercial communications - through the use of automated systems without the intervention of the operator (for example, e-mail), but also through traditional methods of contact, such as the postal service, and through the official pages that Panini manage on the main social media (i.e. Facebook and Instagram)- that are the most relevant and least invasive possible, limiting as far as possible the circumstance that you receive messages not of your interest
(Profiling)
.
D- Lawful Basis for Processing Personal Data, Mandatory/Discretionary Provision of Personal Data and  Consequences in case of not providing
The lawful basis for processing the Personal Data, in accordance with the purposes set in the earlier Section of this Privacy Policy (“Purposes of the Data Processing”), is as follows. The provision of Personal Data and the related processing for the purposes related to
Services Provision
and
Contractual Obligations
, is strictly functional to the performance of the requested Service and the correct execution of the contractual relationship with you and therefore they constitute a necessary condition for the establishment of the contractual relationship itself and the lawful basis of the processing. Consequently, failure to provide the Personal Data requested for this purpose, or the inaccuracy of the data provided, will make it impossible for Panini to carry out the service and the contractual relationship and would legitimize Panini to refuse to carry it out.
The provision of Personal Data, and the related processing for purposes related to
Legal Compliance
, is necessary for Panini in order to comply with the related legal obligations. When you provide your Personal Data to Panini, we must process them in accordance with applicable laws which may include the storage and communication to the competent authorities for compliance with tax, customs or other obligations.
The provision of Personal Data, and the related processing for purposes related to
Security Activities
is based on the interest of Panini to identify and prevent illegal conduct and for related assessment of responsability in case of cybercrime against the Website or the Application of Panini or third parties.
The provision of Personal Data, and the related processing, for the purposes related to the activity of
Soft Spam
is based on the legitimate interest of Panini to send marketing communications via e-mail regarding products and services similar to those you have already used or purchased through the application. You can stop the receipt of these communications without suffering any consequence (other than that of not being able to receive further communications of this kind by Panini) using the link at the bottom of each of the e-mails received for that purpose.
The provision of Personal Data, and the related processing of such data for the purposes related to the
Marketing
activity, is based on your explicit consent collected through a specific checkbox. You are not forced to provide such consent to Panini and, if you do so, you are free to withdraw it at any time without suffering any consequence (other than not receiving marketing communications from Panini can withdraw your consent for this purpose by following the instructions contained in the "
Data Subjects’ Rights
" section of this Privacy Policy.
The provision of Personal Data, and the related processing, for the purposes related to the Profiling activity is based on your explicit consent collected through a specific checkbox. You are not obliged to provide such consent to Panini and, if you do so, you are free to revoke it at any time without suffering any consequence (other than not being able to benefit from the personalization of Panini's commercial offers). You can withdraw your consent for this purpose by following the instructions provided in the "
Data Subjects’ Rights
" section of this Privacy Policy.
E- Personal Data Sharing
The Personal Data will be made known to the Panini staff in charge of the development and management of the Website and Application that is authorized to process them for the purpose of achieving the aforementioned purposes and who are committed to confidentiality or otherwise have received an appropriate legal obligation to confidentiality.
Personal Data may be shared, used and transferred within the companies belonging to the Panini group for accounting and administrative purposes.
Personal Data will be made known to third parties, appointed as Data Processors, if they process Data on behalf of Panini (for example, companies responsible for managing and processing sales orders, suppliers with whom it is necessary to interact for the
Service Provision
such as hosting providers, platform providers for sending e-mails or, again, suppliers who perform technical maintenance activities including the maintenance of network equipment and electronic communications networks, software developers for the payment systems, suppliers providing the technological platform and payment gateway for orders for products in the e-payments area, payment service providers for e-payments activities).
Personal Data may be shared with third parties with whom Panini has ongoing contractual relationships concerning services functional to the performance of the activity (such as couriers for the delivery of products, audit firms, persons, companies or professional firms that provide assistance and advice on the subject, administrative, legal, tax, financial and credit recovery firms relating to the provision of the Services).
Finally, Personal Data will be communicated when requested to the competent taxation offices, or to other public bodies, according to the provisions of the laws in force.
Personal Data is not intended for publication or dissemination.
F- Personal Data Transfer
Given the international presence of Panini, some of your Personal Data may be shared with recipients, referred to in the previous paragraph, which could be found in countries outside the the European Economic Area. Panini ensures that the processing of your Personal Data by these parties will be in compliance with applicable law. Therefore, the transfers will be made with adequate guarantees, such as adequacy decisions, models of Standard Contractual Clauses approved by the European Commission or other guarantees considered adequate.
More information is available by writing to Panini at the following address:
webprivacy@panini.it
G- Personal Data Retention
The Personal Data processed for the purpose of
Services Provision
and
Contractual Obligations
will be retained by Panini for the time strictly necessary for the execution of the requested service and for the correct execution of the contractual relationship with you. As this Personal Data is processed to provide you with the Services and allow the execution of the contractual relationship, Panini may keep them for a longer period, in particular for what may be necessary in order to protect the interests of Panini against possible claims arising from the
Services Provision
.
In any case, Panini specifies that the retention time related to any orders and purchases you have made is equal to 6 months. Panini, moreover, specifies that it will keep your authentication credentials to the Wesbite and the Application Services up to 54 months from the date of the last login (the underlying logic is that Panini has calculated that the retention time identified is considered reasonable for the participation or creation of a digital sticker albums as it approximates the frequency of the publication of an annual digital sticker collection). At the end of this period the data will be made anonymous.
Your requests, and the data contained in them, collected through the Contacts/Customer Service area of the Applications will be maintained for one year from the closure of the request in order to allow Panini to handle any additional requests received after closure. At the end of this period the Data that permit the identification, even indirect, of a physical person (such as name, surname, e-mail) will be made anonymous and maintained, only in the form of aggregated data, for statistical purposes
The Personal Data processed for the purposes of
Legal Compliance
will be retained by Panini for the period envisaged by specific legal obligations or applicable legislation.
Personal Data processed for the purposes of
Security
will be retained by Panini for the strictly required timing for this specific purpose and therefore Panini have to keep them to protect itself and communicate those Data to competent authorities.
The Personal Data processed for the purpose of
Soft Spam
will be kept by Panini until you object to the process through the link found at the bottom of each of the Soft Spam e-mails sent.
The Personal Data processed for the purposes of
Marketing and Profiling
will be retained by Panini until the revocation of the consent you have given and renewed periodically. Once your consent is withdrawn, Panini will no longer use your Personal Data for such purposes, but may retain them, particularly as may be necessary in order to protect Panini interests from possible liability based on such processing.
Panini informs you that, in order to respond to the principle of limitation of conservation, the data processed for the purposes of Marketing and Profiling will in any case be maintained for a maximum of 54 months from the date of the last login in accordance with the logic used for the retention of authentication credentials to the Site Services referred to above.
H- Data Subject Rights
At any time you are entitled, as Data subject, to:
request access to your Personal Data, (and/or a copy of such Personal Data), as well as further information on the current treatment of them;
request the correction or updating of your Personal Data processed by Panini, where they are incomplete or out of date;
request the deletion of your Personal Data from the Panini databases, where you deem the processing unnecessary or illegitimate;
request the limitation of the processing of your Personal Data by Panini, where you believe that your Personal Information is not correct, necessary or is unlawfully processed, or if you had opposed its processing;
exercise the right to data portability, i.e. to obtain a copy of the Personal Data supplied to Panini that relates to you in a structured format, for common use and readable by an automatic device, or to request transmission to another Data Controller;
oppose the processing of your Personal Data, using a legal basis relating to your particular situation, which you believe should prevent Panini from processing your Personal Data;
revoke your consent for purposes of Marketing and Profiling  and to oppose processing for the purpose of Soft Spam. Please remember that consent expressed by sending promotional communications for Marketing and Profiling purposes extends not only to communications sent using automated systems without an operator (e.g. email), but also via traditional contact methods, e.g. postal services and telephone. You can always revoke your consent to processing, even separately, e.g. by deciding to receive communications only by post and not via automated systems such as email, or also by blocking the use of third party profiling cookies on Panini Websites to stop receiving such communications;
revoke your consent to cookies for Profiling purposes when you use the Site, acting on the Settings button in the appropriate banner, always reacheble by clicking the following symbol
and/or
(Manage Cookies)
placed in the footer of the Site.
Please note that the Personal Data you provided to Panini may be changed at any time, through the "modify data" section of the Applications or by writing to:
webprivacy@panini.it
In particular, if the information provided by you is not sufficient to identify you unambiguously and / or with a sufficient degree of certainty, taking into account the specific type of right exercised (such as, in particular, those of access, copy and cancellation), Panini will request further information from you as required by specific regulatory provisions regarding the protection of personal data. In the event that Panini detects the absence or lack of suitable data to identify you and therefore there are reasonable doubts about your identity, Panini may then ask you to provide a copy of an identification document or any additional information deemed useful for your identification. In the event that you provide such a document, personal details such as your first and last name and your address should be clear in order to be able to identify you correctly, while any other information such as your photo or any other personal characteristics not necessary for identification should be removed or obscured before sending. We specify that our use of the information on your identity document is strictly limited to fully accounting for your request: in fact, such Data will be used only to verify your identity and will not be kept for longer than necessary for this purpose.
You may exercise the above rights by means of the methods indicated above.
You can also stop receiving
Soft Spam
using the appropriate link at the bottom of each e-mail received (via the " Unsubscribe " button).
We inform you that for Marketing purposes you can revoke and terminate at any time the sending of this commercial information, by writing to the email address indicated above or, in the case of communications received through IT tools, following the procedure indicated at the bottom of the communication (via the "Unsubscribe" button).
Consent for the purpose Profiling can be revoked by changing, at any time, the preferences of the user profile within the Website or by writing to the e-mail address
webprivacy@panini.it
.
As regards Marketing  via push notifications on your device (if you are using the Application), you can revoke your consent via the settings on your Device. More specifically, on an iOS device you need to go to "Settings", then "Notification centre", select the App and disable the relevant notifications. If you have an Android Device, go to "Settings", scroll to the bottom to "Notifications", use "Show All" or "Sent recently" to select the App and block notifications via "Show/Consent Notifications".
Panini also informs you that you always have the right to lodge a complaint with the competent Supervisory Authority (for example that of the State in which you have your habitual residence, in Italy the Guarantor for the Protection of Personal Data) if you believe that the processing of your data is contrary to the legislation in the field of personal data protection actually applicable.
I- Privacy Policy Amendments
This Privacy Policy version 1.0 is effective from August 2023. Panini reserves the right to modify or simply update its content, in part or completely, also due to changes in the applicable legislation. Panini will be able to inform you of these changes as soon as they are introduced and they will be binding as soon as they are published on the Website or on the Application. Panini invites you to visit this section regularly to get to know the most recent and updated version of the Privacy Policy in order to be always updated on the Personal Data collected and on the use that Panini makes of them.
